---
description: OPC UA bridge and BMS deployment patterns for chiller anomaly detection
globs: app/opcua_bridge.py,app/preprocessor.py,docker-compose.yml
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use `asyncua` for all OPC UA client code in this project.
- All 16 sensor keys in `NODE_MAP` must match `RAW_SENSOR_COLS` in `app/preprocessor.py`.
- Never hardcode node IDs outside `NODE_MAP` in `app/opcua_bridge.py`.
- Timestamps passed to `ChillerPreprocessor.update()` must be timezone-aware UTC.
- Do not POST to `/predict` until `preprocessor.is_warm()` returns true (48 readings).
- Feature vector order must follow `FEATURE_ORDER` — never reorder for convenience.
- Scaler (`model/scaler.pkl`) must be applied in the preprocessor, not in the inference API.
- Log connection failures with server URL; never log credentials or certificate contents.
- `handle_anomaly()` is the extension point for alerts — keep read/score paths side-effect free.
- Training pipeline parity is mandatory: verify preprocessing matches the training notebook before blaming the ONNX model.
